<biogHist>
<abstract>A habitual truant is a child who is constantly absent from school. The Education Act 1926 contained a provision under which a child could be charged with being a habitual truant and placed under the control of the State Children's Council and its successors. This provision was repealed in 1993. It was again included in the Children's Protection Act 1993 as part of the definition of a child at risk.</abstract>

